1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Twenty-four Australians arrive on the tropical island of Samoa ready to battle the elements and each other in order to win the A$500,000 prize and the title of Sole Survivor.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: The tribes compete in an Immunity Challenge to avoid tribal council where they will be forced to vote a teammate off the island. Who will be the second contestant to leave the island?

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: A physical Reward Challenge pushes the tribes to their limits for a tarp & cushions. Later, the Immunity Challenge sees the tribes compete on a puzzle to avoid heading to Tribal Council.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: One tribe is struggling to make fire and morale is at an all-time low. They must win the Immunity Challenge to lift their spirits and avoid Tribal Council, from where another contestant will be voted off the island.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: Facing elimination, the three tribes head to the immunity challenge. Which team will return to their camp triumphant, and which teams will be left to ponder what happened at Tribal Council?

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: The tribes are still reeling after the previous night's Tribal Council, but they will need to put their differences aside and unite to compete in an epic immunity challenge.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: The reward challenge will set tummies rumbling as the contestants compete for a barbecue feast. In the immunity challenge, each tribe will be challenged to carry their own weight to avoid Tribal Council.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: The Saanapu tribe are on edge following another tense elimination. One of their contestants is feeling increasingly insecure about their place in the tribe. Will they be the next person to be voted out?

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: As the dust from the previous Tribal Council settles, some contestants feel anxious about their position in the game and scramble to make new alliances.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: One contestant is left feeling shocked and guilty after the previous night's Tribal Council. The result causes a rift in the tribe, and a very obvious division between some contestants.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: After receiving a vote at Tribal Council, one contestant is shocked after he survives the vote. He is angry and hurt, but does he have the numbers to seek revenge?

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: Tribal tension continues to escalate when two people come to blows over their sleeping arrangements. With the losing team being sent to Tribal Council, who will become the next person to leave the island?

13.title: Episode #1.13
13.plot: Which tribe can muster the strength to win the Reward Challenge for a huge traditional Samoan feast? Jonathan reveals a massive twist that will give one tribe a huge advantage in the game.

14.title: Episode #1.14
14.plot: One castaway wakes the morning after Tribal Council furious that their strategy has been exposed, while others bask in their new found power as they head into the next challenge for a reward and immunity.

15.title: Episode #1.15
15.plot: One tribe is still shocked after the last Tribal Council, but they try and rally each other back together anticipating another immunity challenge in order to avoid elimination.

16.title: Episode #1.16
16.plot: After the merge of the two tribes into one, the contestants jostle for position to control the game. With power being held by a select few, one contestant sets on a plan to change the game, but will it be too little too late?

17.title: Episode #1.17
17.plot: One castaway is furious after the previous night's Tribal Council and is determined to get revenge. At the Reward Challenge, Jonathan announces that the winning team will each receive a letter from home.

18.title: Episode #1.18
18.plot: The previous night's Tribal Council has left alliances exposed and the tribe in turmoil. For some of the castaways, paranoia sets in. Will they have to turn on each other just to keep themselves in the game?

19.title: Episode #1.19
19.plot: The remaining castaways face a Reward Challenge for a delicious Sunday roast which will be the perfect fuel for the Immunity Challenge. Who will be safe from the next Tribal Council vote?

20.title: Episode #1.20
20.plot: Tribal politics continue to escalate, but one castaway thinks that their back is against the wall and no amount of scrambling can save them. Will that person receive a lifeline?

21.title: Episode #1.21
21.plot: Some of the castaways are furious about the accusations made at the previous Tribal Council. Now that the jury are able to watch the discussions play out, will it have an impact on their chance of winning the game?

22.title: Episode #1.22
22.plot: With alliances hanging in the balance, the castaways head to the Reward Challenge in an effort to win a night at a luxury spa. Who will be the next person to be voted out and become a member of the jury?

23.title: Episode #1.23
23.plot: Emotions are running high now that the castaways are getting closer to the finale. They are starting to second guess their strategies. Is now a good time to switch?

24.title: Episode #1.24
24.plot: A group of contestants are marooned in an isolated location, where they must provide food, water, fire, and shelter for themselves. The contestants compete in challenges for rewards and immunity from elimination. The contestants are progressively eliminated from the game as they are voted out by their fellow contestants until only one remains and is awarded the title of "Sole Australian Survivor" and the cash grand prize.

25.title: Episode #1.25
25.plot: A group of contestants are marooned in an isolated location, where they must provide food, water, fire, and shelter for themselves. The contestants compete in challenges for rewards and immunity from elimination. The contestants are progressively eliminated from the game as they are voted out by their fellow contestants until only one remains and is awarded the title of "Sole Australian Survivor" and the cash grand prize.

26.title: Episode #1.26
26.plot: A group of contestants are marooned in an isolated location, where they must provide food, water, fire, and shelter for themselves. The contestants compete in challenges for rewards and immunity from elimination. The contestants are progressively eliminated from the game as they are voted out by their fellow contestants until only one remains and is awarded the title of "Sole Australian Survivor" and the cash grand prize.

1.title: Episode #2.1
1.plot: Twenty-four new Australians arrive on the tropical island of Samoa ready to outwit, outplay and outlast each other in order to win the A$500,000 prize and the title of Sole Survivor.

2.title: Episode #2.2
2.plot: The perfect storm is brewing in Samoa as the tribes fight to protect their supplies and maintain their fire under adverse conditions. How will the prospect of a possible idol in play tamper with the newly-formed friendships?

3.title: Episode #2.3
3.plot: As a major alliance crumbles, one tribe scrambles to avoid elimination. The other tribe become frustrated with two of its members and make moves to ensure that they are the next to go.

4.title: Episode #2.4
4.plot: Food is the only thing on the castaways' minds as one person from each tribe faces a moral dilemma which could have dramatic ramifications for their own games and for the other castaways.

5.title: Episode #2.5
5.plot: Tensions run high as the castaways endure further wind and rain without fire and shelter, then face an Immunity Challenge that requires endurance and sends the losing tribe to Tribal Council.

6.title: Episode #2.6
6.plot: Some blatant lies at the previous Tribal Council have put everyone in one of the camps on edge. Will they be able to put their differences aside to win the Reward Challenge, or will they leave hungry?

7.title: Episode #2.7
7.plot: The previous night's brutal Tribal Council has left one castaway on the war path seeking retribution. At the Immunity Challenge, the tribes must take part in a physical Sumo-an contest.

8.title: Episode #2.8
8.plot: As both tribes appear to reach their wits' end, the prospect of a luxurious and cleansing reward could be enough to keep the castaways in the game for weeks to come.

9.title: Episode #2.9
9.plot: Winning Immunity has never been so vital to resettling the balance within each of the tribes, and when the challenge to win it is highly competitive and encourages fair contact, things are certain to get feisty.

10.title: Episode #2.10
10.plot: Social divisions begin to exhaust the castaways as one tribe breaks down before the Immunity Challenge. Will they be able to come together and avoid another visit to Tribal Council?

11.title: Episode #2.11
11.plot: An alliance of castaways find themselves at each other's throats over who is doing enough work around their camp, but is one player deliberately acting lazy in order to divide the tribe?

12.title: Episode #2.12
12.plot: A surprise challenge sees one castaway return to camp with an unexpected power that could push tensions to breaking point. Later, will one castaway past come back to haunt them at tribal council?

13.title: Episode #2.13
13.plot: Alliances continue to flip as a former power player finds themselves at the bottom of their tribe, and a last minute scramble to return to their former glory will turn friend against friend.

14.title: Episode #2.14
14.plot: Betrayal runs rampant within both tribes as deceptive immunity clues and relentless strategising begins to place targets on the backs of castaways who had previously flown under the radar.

15.title: Episode #2.15
15.plot: The fallout from one of the most dramatic Tribal Councils this season sends shockwaves through one tribe as castaways scramble to repair broken bonds.

16.title: Episode #2.16
16.plot: Change is in the air as time comes for the biggest event in the game so far: a merger. Emotions continue to run high when a particularly difficult reward challenge offers a deeply sentimental prize.

17.title: Episode #2.17
17.plot: The fallout from the first group tribal council tears a rift between the newly formed tribe, resulting in a huge clash of alliances. Who will be the next contestant to have their flame extinguished?

18.title: Episode #2.18
18.plot: A shock display of power at the last tribal council places an immediate target on one castaway. Will the new shift in camp dynamics be enough to remove a prolific player from the game?

19.title: Episode #2.19
19.plot: A scheming conversation is overheard, putting one contestant in the firing line, and an alliance is shattered, resulting in one of the most divided tribal councils this series.

20.title: Episode #2.20
20.plot: Another alliance is in jeopardy as one contestant decides to flip on a fellow tribesman, planning the biggest blindside this season, but an unexpected turn of events forces the castaway to reconsider.

21.title: Episode #2.21
21.plot: The battle for individual immunity is at an all-time high and contestants must compete in a fast-paced memory challenge to secure their safety for another day going into tribal council.

22.title: Episode #2.22
22.plot: With alliances crumbling and paranoia setting in, all six castaways are determined to win individual immunity. In an explosive Tribal Council, one contestant holds the power, but who will they choose?

23.title: Episode #2.23
23.plot: After seven weeks on the island of Samoa, only five contestants remain in the race towards winning $500,000 in prize money. Who will become the next member of the Jury?

24.title: Episode #2.24
24.plot: After 50 testing days on the island of Samoa, the final four contestants go into the challenge, not for immunity but for an advantage: to eliminate a member of the jury at Tribal Council.

25.title: Episode #2.25
25.plot: The final four start to plan and collude on who they will vote off next at Tribal Council, but this is Survivor, and anybody could win immunity.

26.title: Episode #2.26
26.plot: With only three castaways remaining, who will win the $500,000 prize and the title of sole survivor?

27.title: Episode #2.27
27.plot: Following the exciting winner reveal to crown Australian Survivor champion for 2017, 24 castaways reunite for an explosive reunion special hosted by Jonathan LaPaglia.

imdb.plot outline: Australian Survivor is a game show where 24 everyday Australians are divided into three tribes and are on an island with little more than the clothes on their backs and must survive for 55 days. These people compete in challenges for rewards and, more importantly, immunity. At the end of each day, one person will be voted out. Throughout this game, there will be a series of advantages that will help people get further in the game. One of these people will outwit, outplay & outlast the others to win the title of Sole Survivor and the grand prize of $500000.
